Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Matchmaking \Match"mak`ing\, n. 1. The act or process of making matches for kindling or burning. [1913 Webster]
2. The act or process of trying to bring about a marriage for others. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Matchmaking \Match"mak`ing\, a. Busy in making or contriving marriages; as, a matchmaking woman. [1913 Webster]
